---

Critical CK issue:

Loading too many records at once will result in:

.rdata:00000001438525D0	00000042	C	OUT OF HANDLE ARRAY ENTRIES.  Null handle created for pointer %p.

The only real solution to this is to generate (or cut down) plugins that have *only* CELLs which contain REFRs pointing to STAT or SCOL base objects. The entire goal is to reduce the amount of handles each plugin requires so that multiple plugins can be loaded at once without hitting the limit.

---

Figure out what to do with each master's Vis files that aren't part of the Commonwealth. Surely there will be worldspace mods outside of the Commonwealth, so it shouldn't just be focused only on that, but how to handle generated files that aren't actually different than the vanilla files? Precombines are hashed (somehow) so they *should* be safe to detect for uniqueness. UVDs are per cell and not hashed, however they affect a 3x3 grid of cells and if any of the cells sharing the same RVIS key are altered from vanilla then the newly generated UVD file must be used.

Cross check all references in XPRI data out there to determine what to keep beyond static REFRs.

