Note: It seems that CK will in some cases (particularly XPRI) create references with initial master load id offset from 08 forward as if every official master were loaded before it even if they weren't when generating the plugin from within CK. Update: actually this may not be true and I just forgot that I had initially loaded all 8 esms in my test. Update to update: Actually what seems to be going on here is that if a plugin passed to CK has a master that loads another master, it throws off the entire indexing of CK for the generated plugin. The only real workaround is to ensure the plugin used with CK (as a target to -generateprecombined or -generateprevisdata) has all masters as they would be in final form.

