If every master involved with a given plugin does *not* have the same order of masters that the loaded plugin has CK will seem to load them in this kind of order:

1. All masters of the last master are loaded:

Data File Loaded 'Fallout4.esm'...
Data File Loaded 'DLCRobot.esm'...
Data File Loaded 'DLCworkshop01.esm'...
Data File Loaded 'DLCCoast.esm'...
Data File Loaded 'DLCworkshop02.esm'...
Data File Loaded 'DLCworkshop03.esm'...
Data File Loaded 'DLCNukaWorld.esm'...
Data File Loaded 'ReGrowth Overhaul 10.esm'...
Data File Loaded 'rgo_tree_noocclude.esm'...

aka

ckgen.build/10/Data/America Rising - A Tale of the Enclave.esm:
[00] Fallout4.esm
[01] DLCRobot.esm
[02] DLCworkshop01.esm
[03] DLCCoast.esm
[04] DLCworkshop02.esm
[05] DLCworkshop03.esm
[06] DLCNukaWorld.esm
[07] ReGrowth Overhaul 10.esm
[08] rgo_tree_noocclude.esm

2. Then the first master:

Data File Loaded 'America Rising - A Tale of the Enclave.esm'...

3. Then every other master of the loaded plugin in reverse order:

[09] Unofficial Fallout 4 Patch.esm
[10] 3DNPC_FO4.esm
[11] AA FusionCityRising.esm
[12] AA FusionCityRising - HotC.esm
[13] AA 50 Ways To Die.esm
[14] OutcastsAndRemnants.esm
[15] WelcometoGoodneighbor.esm
[16] BTInteriors_Project.esm
[17] stumbleuponinteriors.esm
[18] crowdedcommonwealth.esm
[19] plenty 'o' exploration.esm
[20] moreXplore.esm
[21] Convenient Bridges.esm
[22] America Rising - A Tale of the Enclave.esm <--- but not included this as it was the first master loaded

It seems to be using some kind of graphing based decision which means if all masters involved aren't also locked down in master order one may get non-determinant loading orders.

