One can see the depth based loading where once it gets to 'AA FusionCityRising.esm' it proceeds to then load that plugin's masters first and then back to 'AA FusionCityRising.esm' (which 'AA FusionCityRising - HotC.esm' also has as a master). Now 'data file loaded' doesn't necessarily mean it parses each plugin's forms in that order, but the output of CombinedObjects.esp seems to infer it does:

ckgen.build/1/Data/CombinedObjects.esp:
[00] Fallout4.esm
[01] DLCRobot.esm
[02] DLCworkshop01.esm
[03] DLCCoast.esm
[04] DLCworkshop02.esm
[05] DLCworkshop03.esm
[06] DLCNukaWorld.esm
[07] ReGrowth Overhaul 10.esp
[08] rgo_tree_noocclude.esp
[09] America Rising - A Tale of the Enclave.esp
[10] Convenient Bridges.esp
[11] moreXplore.esp
[12] plenty 'o' exploration.esp
[13] crowdedcommonwealth.esp
[14] stumbleuponinteriors.esp
[15] BTInteriors_Project.esp
[16] WelcometoGoodneighbor.esp
[17] OutcastsAndRemnants.esp
[18] AA 50 Ways To Die.esp
[19] 3DNPC_FO4.esp
[20] Unofficial Fallout 4 Patch.esp
[21] AA FusionCityRising.esp
[22] AA FusionCityRising - HotC.esp
[23] America Rising - A Tale of the Enclave.esp.pcv.esp

I think that nearly 99% of the time this doesn't actually cause an issue because most mods aren't modifying the exact same statics or scols but are instead, when loaded together, resulting in a composite of all references which precombine/previs is aware of when generating. However, it's not as robust as it should be and ensuring each master has the explicit master order of things involved with it might be safest.

Update: this is actually a problem, with the following test:

ckgen.build/2/Data/BurningCampfiresThatHurt.esp.pcv.esm:
