Problem?

STAT objects referenced by SCOL objects but the SCOL is defined in a master. Regenerating SCOL for the overriding plugin won't do anything because it is not defining any SCOLs itself and as such when that SCOL is generated it won't have any knowledge of a child plugin that's overriding one of it's statics. Not sure if this causes hard breakage or just makes it so later STAT overrides have no effect if they're involved with a SCOL from a master and said SCOL is precombined or (if not precombined), already using generated SCOL data.

It might be prudent to look for any plugin that creates/overrides STAT or SCOL data and consider this as a plugin that should be included for pcvgen purposes (i.e. not just plugins with CELL data).

